snippet.textDisplay:
A story about My relationship with Durian.

I was a kid and I despise the smell and the taste. Whenever we walked or drove by a place where they sell durian, I'd pinched my nose right away. Everytime my dad brought durion home, my brother, my mom, and my dad of course, enjoyed it so much while I was dying.

Then I decided it was enough. I legit was fighting myself the first time I tried it. It took me a while to process whatever I was tasting. I'm telling you that it was love on the first taste and never looked back since. A kid who hate durian? Who is that? How could you?!

Durian is love, durian is life.
